  "doc_id": "15603",
  "text": "Parameters measured in all patients included modified H-Y stage and UPDRS-III scores for extrapyramidal signs, as well as plasma concentrations of high-sensitivity CRP. In PD patients with \"on-off\" or \"wearing-off\" phenomena, modified H-Y stage and UPDRS-III scores were determined during an \"on period\". Data on daily doses of L-dopa, entacapone, dopamine agonists, selegiline, and amantadine, and the use of anti-psychotic drugs, were recorded. L-dopa equivalent doses (LEDs) for each of the above agents were calculated as described [CITATION_1] .",
